
# Lab Overview

## Objective

The objective of this lab is to simulate a small SOC workflow by collecting Windows endpoint logs and reviewing them in a centralized platform.

## Components

### Windows 10 VM
Acts as the monitored endpoint. This machine generates Windows Security events and Sysmon telemetry.

### Ubuntu Server VM
Hosts the Wazuh Manager and dashboard for centralized log collection and analysis.

## Data Flow

Windows 10 Endpoint -> Wazuh Agent -> Wazuh Manager -> Dashboard / Alerts

## Why This Design

This design is intentionally small so it is easy to build, understand, and explain in interviews. It focuses on core SOC concepts:

- Endpoint telemetry
- Centralized monitoring
- Alert review
- Basic incident investigation

## Detection Coverage

Current detections focus on:
- Failed authentication
- Suspicious process execution
- User account changes

## Future Improvements

Possible future improvements include:
- Adding a second endpoint
- Adding Sysmon tuning
- Building custom Wazuh rules
- Adding Sigma-to-Wazuh mapping
- Adding Active Directory
